<db:section xml:id="details">
<db:title>Detailed Description</db:title>
<db:para>The <db:link xlink:href="qml-qtquick3d-particles3d-spriteparticle3d.xml">SpriteParticle3D</db:link> is a logical particle element that creates particles from a 2D sprite texture.</db:para>
</db:section>
<db:section xml:id="property-documentation">
<db:title>Property Documentation</db:title>
<db:section xml:id="BlendMode-prop">
<db:title>BlendMode : enumeration</db:title>
<db:fieldsynopsis>
<db:type>enumeration</db:type>
<db:varname>BlendMode</db:varname>
<db:modifier>writable</db:modifier>
<db:synopsisinfo role="access">public</db:synopsisinfo>
<db:synopsisinfo role="status">active</db:synopsisinfo>
<db:synopsisinfo role="threadsafeness">unspecified</db:synopsisinfo>
</db:fieldsynopsis>
<db:para>Defines the blending mode for the particles.</db:para>
<db:informaltable>
<db:thead>
<db:tr>
<db:th>Constant</db:th>
<db:th>Description</db:th>
</db:tr>
</db:thead>
<db:tr>
<db:td>
<db:para>SpriteParticle3D.SourceOver</db:para>
</db:td>
<db:td>
<db:para>Blend particles with SourceOver mode.</db:para>
</db:td>
</db:tr>
<db:tr>
<db:td>
<db:para>SpriteParticle3D.Screen</db:para>
</db:td>
<db:td>
<db:para>Blend particles with Screen mode.</db:para>
</db:td>
</db:tr>
<db:tr>
<db:td>
<db:para>SpriteParticle3D.Multiply</db:para>
</db:td>
<db:td>
<db:para>Blend particles with Multiply mode.</db:para>
</db:td>
</db:tr>
</db:informaltable>
</db:section>
<db:section xml:id="billboard-prop">
<db:title>billboard : bool</db:title>
<db:fieldsynopsis>
<db:type>bool</db:type>
<db:varname>billboard</db:varname>
<db:modifier>writable</db:modifier>
<db:synopsisinfo role="access">public</db:synopsisinfo>
<db:synopsisinfo role="status">active</db:synopsisinfo>
<db:synopsisinfo role="threadsafeness">unspecified</db:synopsisinfo>
</db:fieldsynopsis>
<db:para>This property defines if the particle texture should always be aligned face towards the screen.</db:para>
<db:note>
<db:para>When set to <db:code>true</db:code>, <db:link xlink:href="qml-qtquick3d-particles3d-particle3d.xml">Particle3D</db:link> <db:link xlink:href="qml-qtquick3d-particles3d-particle3d.xml#alignMode-prop">alignMode</db:link> property does not have an effect.</db:para>
</db:note>
<db:para>The default value is <db:code>false</db:code>.</db:para>
</db:section>
<db:section xml:id="blendMode-propx">
<db:title>blendMode : BlendMode</db:title>
<db:fieldsynopsis>
<db:type>BlendMode</db:type>
<db:varname>blendMode</db:varname>
<db:modifier>writable</db:modifier>
<db:synopsisinfo role="access">public</db:synopsisinfo>
<db:synopsisinfo role="status">active</db:synopsisinfo>
<db:synopsisinfo role="threadsafeness">unspecified</db:synopsisinfo>
</db:fieldsynopsis>
<db:para>This property defines the blending mode used for rendering the particles.</db:para>
<db:para>The default value is <db:code>SpriteParticle3D.SourceOver</db:code>.</db:para>
</db:section>
<db:section xml:id="castsReflections-prop">
<db:title>[since 6.4] castsReflections : bool</db:title>
<db:fieldsynopsis>
<db:type>bool</db:type>
<db:varname>castsReflections</db:varname>
<db:modifier>writable</db:modifier>
<db:synopsisinfo role="access">public</db:synopsisinfo>
<db:synopsisinfo role="status">active</db:synopsisinfo>
<db:synopsisinfo role="threadsafeness">unspecified</db:synopsisinfo>
</db:fieldsynopsis>
<db:para>When this property is set to <db:code>true</db:code>, the sprite is rendered by reflection probes and can be seen in the reflections.</db:para>
<db:para>This property was introduced in Qt 6.4.</db:para>
</db:section>
<db:section xml:id="colorTable-prop">
<db:title>colorTable : Texture</db:title>
<db:fieldsynopsis>
<db:type>Texture</db:type>
<db:varname>colorTable</db:varname>
<db:modifier>writable</db:modifier>
<db:synopsisinfo role="access">public</db:synopsisinfo>
<db:synopsisinfo role="status">active</db:synopsisinfo>
<db:synopsisinfo role="threadsafeness">unspecified</db:synopsisinfo>
</db:fieldsynopsis>
<db:para>This property defines the <db:link xlink:href="qml-qtquick3d-texture.xml">Texture</db:link> used for coloring the particles. The image can be a 1D or a 2D texture. Horizontal pixels determine the particle color over its <db:link xlink:href="qml-qtquick3d-particles3d-particleemitter3d.xml#lifeSpan-prop">lifeSpan</db:link>. For example, when the particle is halfway through its life, it will have the color specified halfway across the image. If the image is 2D, vertical row is randomly selected for each particle. For example, a c {256 x 4} image contains <db:code>4</db:code> different coloring options for particles.</db:para>
</db:section>
<db:section xml:id="lights-prop">
<db:title>[since 6.3] lights : list&lt;Light&gt;</db:title>
<db:fieldsynopsis>
<db:type>list&lt;Light&gt;</db:type>
<db:varname>lights</db:varname>
<db:modifier>writable</db:modifier>
<db:synopsisinfo role="access">public</db:synopsisinfo>
<db:synopsisinfo role="status">active</db:synopsisinfo>
<db:synopsisinfo role="threadsafeness">unspecified</db:synopsisinfo>
</db:fieldsynopsis>
<db:para>This property contains a list of <db:link xlink:href="qml-qtquick3d-light.xml">lights</db:link> used for rendering the particles.</db:para>
<db:note>
<db:para>For optimal performance, define lights only if they are needed and keep the amount of lights at minimum.</db:para>
</db:note>
<db:para>This property was introduced in Qt 6.3.</db:para>
</db:section>
<db:section xml:id="offsetX-prop">
<db:title>[since 6.3] offsetX : float</db:title>
<db:fieldsynopsis>
<db:type>float</db:type>
<db:varname>offsetX</db:varname>
<db:modifier>writable</db:modifier>
<db:synopsisinfo role="access">public</db:synopsisinfo>
<db:synopsisinfo role="status">active</db:synopsisinfo>
<db:synopsisinfo role="threadsafeness">unspecified</db:synopsisinfo>
</db:fieldsynopsis>
<db:para>This property defines the particles offset in the X axis</db:para>
<db:para>This property was introduced in Qt 6.3.</db:para>
</db:section>
<db:section xml:id="offsetY-prop">
<db:title>[since 6.3] offsetY : float</db:title>
<db:fieldsynopsis>
<db:type>float</db:type>
<db:varname>offsetY</db:varname>
<db:modifier>writable</db:modifier>
<db:synopsisinfo role="access">public</db:synopsisinfo>
<db:synopsisinfo role="status">active</db:synopsisinfo>
<db:synopsisinfo role="threadsafeness">unspecified</db:synopsisinfo>
</db:fieldsynopsis>
<db:para>This property defines the particles offset in the Y axis</db:para>
<db:para>This property was introduced in Qt 6.3.</db:para>
</db:section>
<db:section xml:id="particleScale-prop">
<db:title>particleScale : real</db:title>
<db:fieldsynopsis>
<db:type>real</db:type>
<db:varname>particleScale</db:varname>
<db:modifier>writable</db:modifier>
<db:synopsisinfo role="access">public</db:synopsisinfo>
<db:synopsisinfo role="status">active</db:synopsisinfo>
<db:synopsisinfo role="threadsafeness">unspecified</db:synopsisinfo>
</db:fieldsynopsis>
<db:para>This property defines the scale multiplier of the particles. To adjust the particles sizes in the emitter, use <db:link xlink:href="qml-qtquick3d-particles3d-particleemitter3d.xml">ParticleEmitter3D</db:link> <db:link xlink:href="qml-qtquick3d-particles3d-particleemitter3d.xml#particleScale-prop">particleScale</db:link>, <db:link xlink:href="qml-qtquick3d-particles3d-particleemitter3d.xml#particleEndScale-prop">particleEndScale</db:link>, and <db:link xlink:href="qml-qtquick3d-particles3d-particleemitter3d.xml#particleScaleVariation-prop">particleScaleVariation</db:link> properties.</db:para>
<db:para>The default value is <db:code>5.0</db:code>.</db:para>
</db:section>
<db:section xml:id="sprite-prop">
<db:title>sprite : Texture</db:title>
<db:fieldsynopsis>
<db:type>Texture</db:type>
<db:varname>sprite</db:varname>
<db:modifier>writable</db:modifier>
<db:synopsisinfo role="access">public</db:synopsisinfo>
<db:synopsisinfo role="status">active</db:synopsisinfo>
<db:synopsisinfo role="threadsafeness">unspecified</db:synopsisinfo>
</db:fieldsynopsis>
<db:para>This property defines the <db:link xlink:href="qml-qtquick3d-texture.xml">Texture</db:link> used for the particles.</db:para>
<db:para>For example, to use &quot;snowFlake.png&quot; as the particles texture:</db:para>
<db:programlisting language="qml">SpriteParticle3D {
    id: snowParticle
    ...
    sprite: Texture {
        source: &quot;images/snowflake.png&quot;
    }
}
</db:programlisting>
</db:section>
<db:section xml:id="spriteSequence-prop">
<db:title>spriteSequence : SpriteSequence3D</db:title>
<db:fieldsynopsis>
<db:type>SpriteSequence3D</db:type>
<db:varname>spriteSequence</db:varname>
<db:modifier>writable</db:modifier>
<db:synopsisinfo role="access">public</db:synopsisinfo>
<db:synopsisinfo role="status">active</db:synopsisinfo>
<db:synopsisinfo role="threadsafeness">unspecified</db:synopsisinfo>
</db:fieldsynopsis>
<db:para>This property defines the sprite sequence properties for the particle. If the <db:link xlink:href="qml-qtquick3d-particles3d-spriteparticle3d.xml#sprite-prop">sprite</db:link> texture contains a frame sequence, set this property to define the frame count, animation direction etc. features.</db:para>
</db:section>
